The evidence with the title '7 facts anyone taking birth control should know - Vox ' says Oct 9, 2017  ... All birth control pills use hormones to prevent pregnancy . Some contain a hormone called progestin . Others contain two hormones, progestin and estrogen. All of them work by doing two things : they prevent women from ovulating, and they cause the cervical mucus to thicken , which makes it more difficult  ... 
